---
import Section from "~/components/Section.astro";
import Stage from "~/components/Stage.astro";
import Callout from "~/components/Callout.astro";
---

<Section id="cuckoo" num="07" title="Cuckoo hashing — two levels of it">
  <p>
    BitcoinPIR uses cuckoo hashing at <em>two</em> different levels, and they
    do different jobs. Mixing them up will make the later sections confusing,
    so here's the distinction up front.
  </p>

  <h3>Level 1: PBC group assignment (3 candidate groups)</h3>
  <p>
    Each scripthash gets mapped to
    <strong>3 candidate PBC groups</strong> (Probabilistic Batch Code) — out
    of <code>K=75</code> groups for the INDEX table and <code>K_CHUNK=80</code>
    for CHUNK. This is how the database is <em>batched</em>: the server can
    answer many parallel PIR queries in one round, as long as each real query
    lands in a different group.
  </p>
  <pre><code>// pir-core/src/params.rs:89
num_hashes: 3,    // each item → 3 candidate PBC groups</code></pre>

  <h3>Level 2: In-group cuckoo table (2 hash functions)</h3>
  <p>
    Once an item is placed in one of its 3 candidate groups, it lives inside
    that group's own cuckoo hash table. The <em>in-group</em> table uses
    <strong>2 hash functions</strong> — so an item has exactly 2 possible
    bin positions inside its group, with <code>slots_per_bin</code> slots per
    bin (4 for INDEX, 3 for CHUNK).
  </p>
  <pre><code>// pir-core/src/params.rs:92
cuckoo_num_hashes: 2,   // each item → 2 bins in its group</code></pre>

  <Stage
    caption="A scripthash derives 3 candidate PBC groups. Placement picks one; inside that group, cuckoo hashing picks one of 2 bins."
    label="Two-level cuckoo hashing"
  >
    <svg viewBox="0 0 680 280" role="img"
      aria-label="A scripthash gets mapped to 3 candidate PBC groups; within the chosen group, 2 candidate bins exist."
      data-anim="cuckoo">
      <!-- scripthash -->
      <g transform="translate(14,110)">
        <rect width="130" height="40" rx="6" class="svg-dim" stroke-width="1.5"/>
        <text x="65" y="17" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" class="svg-label">scripthash</text>
        <text x="65" y="31" text-anchor="middle" font-family="ui-monospace, monospace"
          font-size="10" fill="var(--fg)">76a9…ab</text>
      </g>

      <!-- groups -->
      <g transform="translate(200,20)">
        <text x="120" y="-2" text-anchor="middle" class="svg-label">PBC groups (K = 75)</text>
        {Array.from({ length: 15 }).map((_, i) => {
          const candidates = [3, 8, 11];
          const isCand = candidates.includes(i);
          return (
            <g transform={`translate(${(i % 5) * 46}, ${Math.floor(i / 5) * 44})`}>
              <rect x="0" y="12" width="40" height="36" rx="4"
                class={isCand ? "svg-cand" : "svg-bg"}
                stroke={isCand ? "var(--accent)" : "var(--border)"}
                stroke-width={isCand ? "1.5" : "1"}/>
              <text x="20" y="32" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9"
                fill={isCand ? "var(--accent)" : "var(--fg-dim)"}
                font-family="ui-monospace, monospace">g{i}</text>
            </g>
          );
        })}
        <text x="120" y="170" text-anchor="middle" class="svg-label">… and 60 more</text>
      </g>

      <!-- candidate lines -->
      <g class="cand-line" stroke="var(--accent)" stroke-width="1.3" fill="none"
        stroke-dasharray="4 3">
        <line x1="146" y1="130" x2="258" y2="50" class="cl c1"/>
        <line x1="146" y1="130" x2="386" y2="50" class="cl c2"/>
        <line x1="146" y1="130" x2="248" y2="94" class="cl c3"/>
      </g>

      <!-- chosen group → 2 bins -->
      <g transform="translate(480,30)">
        <text x="80" y="-2" text-anchor="middle" class="svg-label">inside group g₈</text>
        <rect x="0" y="10" width="170" height="110" rx="8" class="svg-dim"
          stroke="var(--accent)" stroke-width="1.5"/>
        <!-- bin 0 -->
        <g transform="translate(14,30)" class="bin b0">
          <text x="60" y="-6" text-anchor="middle" class="svg-label">bin h₀</text>
          {Array.from({ length: 4 }).map((_, s) => (
            <rect x={s * 29} y="0" width="26" height="22" rx="3"
              fill={s === 2 ? "var(--accent)" : "var(--bg-elev-2)"}
              stroke={s === 2 ? "var(--accent)" : "var(--border)"}
              stroke-width="1"/>
          ))}
        </g>
        <!-- bin 1 -->
        <g transform="translate(14,74)" class="bin b1">
          <text x="60" y="-6" text-anchor="middle" class="svg-label">bin h₁</text>
          {Array.from({ length: 4 }).map((_, s) => (
            <rect x={s * 29} y="0" width="26" height="22" rx="3"
              fill="var(--bg-elev-2)"
              stroke="var(--border)"
              stroke-width="1"/>
          ))}
        </g>
        <text x="85" y="148" text-anchor="middle" class="svg-label"
          fill="var(--accent)">slot 2 of h₀ contains the item</text>
      </g>

      <!-- placement arrow -->
      <path d="M 400 80 Q 440 80 472 80" stroke="var(--accent)"
        stroke-width="1.5" fill="none" stroke-dasharray="5 3"
        marker-end="url(#arrC)" class="place-arrow"/>
      <defs>
        <marker id="arrC" viewBox="0 0 10 10" refX="8" refY="5"
          markerWidth="5" markerHeight="5" orient="auto">
          <path d="M 0 0 L 10 5 L 0 10 z" fill="var(--accent)"/>
        </marker>
      </defs>
    </svg>
  </Stage>

  <Callout label="Why 3 groups and 2 bins?">
    <p>
      <strong>3 candidate groups</strong> gives the build-time cuckoo
      placement enough elbow room to spread items across groups at high load
      without constant eviction cascades.
      <strong>2 bins within a group</strong> is the standard 2-hash cuckoo —
      a well-understood load-balancing primitive that keeps the in-group
      table compact. A "not found" client has to check both bins; see
      section&nbsp;9.
    </p>
  </Callout>
</Section>

<style>
  [data-anim="cuckoo"] .svg-cand { fill: var(--accent-bg); }
  [data-anim="cuckoo"] .cl, [data-anim="cuckoo"] .place-arrow { opacity: 0; }
  [data-anim="cuckoo"] .bin { opacity: 0; }
  [data-anim="cuckoo"].play .c1 { animation: fadein 0.5s var(--ease) 0.3s forwards; }
  [data-anim="cuckoo"].play .c2 { animation: fadein 0.5s var(--ease) 0.6s forwards; }
  [data-anim="cuckoo"].play .c3 { animation: fadein 0.5s var(--ease) 0.9s forwards; }
  [data-anim="cuckoo"].play .place-arrow { animation: fadein 0.5s var(--ease) 1.4s forwards; }
  [data-anim="cuckoo"].play .b0 { animation: fadein 0.5s var(--ease) 1.8s forwards; }
  [data-anim="cuckoo"].play .b1 { animation: fadein 0.5s var(--ease) 2.1s forwards; }
  @keyframes fadein { to { opacity: 1; } }
  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    [data-anim="cuckoo"] .cl, [data-anim="cuckoo"] .place-arrow,
    [data-anim="cuckoo"] .bin { opacity: 1 !important; }
  }
</style>

<script is:inline>
  document.querySelectorAll('[data-anim="cuckoo"]').forEach((svg) => {
    const stage = svg.closest("[data-stage]");
    const run = () => {
      svg.classList.remove("play");
      void svg.getBoundingClientRect();
      svg.classList.add("play");
    };
    stage?.addEventListener("stage:visible", run);
    svg.addEventListener("click", run);
  });
</script>
